President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key Administration posts. These include Daniel Elliott III for the position of Member and Chairman of the Surface Transportation Board, Lauren McFerran for the position of Member of the National Labor Relations Board, John Mendez for the position of Member and Chairman of the Board of Directors of the Securities Investor Protection Corporation, and Antonio Weiss for the position of Under Secretary for Domestic Finance at the Department of the Treasury. These nominees bring a wealth of experience and expertise to their respective roles, and President Obama is confident that they will help tackle the important challenges facing America.